WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.920
Previously on "Emergence"...
Jo: Kindred has been involved

00:03.920 --> 00:05.880
with kidnapping, burglary,
two murders.

00:05.880 --> 00:07.580
You don't have anything.

00:07.580 --> 00:11.670
Life as you know it
is gonna change.

00:11.670 --> 00:13.380
Benny: Alan Wilkis.

00:13.380 --> 00:14.920
My anonymous source when
I first investigated Kindred.

00:14.920 --> 00:16.540
He's dead?
Sailing accident.

00:16.540 --> 00:17.540
Look into it.

00:17.540 --> 00:19.000
Cancer's back.

00:19.000 --> 00:20.920
We did this before.
We can do it again.

00:20.920 --> 00:22.080
Not this time, honey.

00:22.080 --> 00:23.380
You don't have to decide
right now.

00:23.380 --> 00:25.670
Does she know what she is?
Emily: No.

00:25.670 --> 00:27.670
Telling an AI
it's an AI

00:27.670 --> 00:29.710
effectively destroys
the program.

00:29.710 --> 00:32.380
Kindred: I wanted us to have
somewhere where we could talk.

00:32.380 --> 00:34.540
Why don't I remember you
when I go back?

00:34.540 --> 00:35.710
This is just for us.

00:35.710 --> 00:37.040
Something's wrong.

00:37.040 --> 00:38.670
[ Groans ]
Grandpa, wake up!

00:38.670 --> 00:39.750
[ Horn blares ]

00:39.750 --> 00:42.670
♪♪

00:42.670 --> 00:46.000
You have to tell the truth.
Do you have superpowers?

00:53.500 --> 00:55.460
Focus.

00:55.460 --> 00:56.750
Calm your mind.

00:58.880 --> 01:01.750
Now...

01:01.750 --> 01:03.790
move the cupcake.

01:05.920 --> 01:07.420
Is it moving?

01:09.040 --> 01:10.540
Not yet.

01:12.420 --> 01:14.380
It's not working.

01:14.380 --> 01:15.670
Don't give up.

01:17.670 --> 01:19.120
Just imagine in your mind

01:19.120 --> 01:21.170
like it's floating
off the floor.

01:23.000 --> 01:26.710
♪♪

01:26.710 --> 01:28.580
Think about it, Piper.

01:28.580 --> 01:32.920
♪♪

01:32.920 --> 01:34.040
Jo: Mia, hurry up!

01:37.040 --> 01:38.580
What was that?!

01:38.580 --> 01:40.120
Nothing!
Nothing!

01:40.120 --> 01:42.540
♪♪

01:42.540 --> 01:43.960
[ Both giggle ]

01:47.000 --> 01:49.960
♪♪

01:54.540 --> 01:56.540
I'm letting Mia
stay home from school today.

01:56.540 --> 01:57.960
Alleged stomachache.

01:57.960 --> 02:00.080
Smart choice.
Vague symptoms.

02:00.080 --> 02:01.830
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, it's fine.

02:01.830 --> 02:03.250
We could all
use a day off.

02:03.250 --> 02:05.210
[ Keys rattle ]

02:07.460 --> 02:09.080
[ Keys clatter ]

02:11.210 --> 02:12.750
[ Silverware clinks ]

02:15.040 --> 02:17.120
Don't you
have to get going?

02:17.120 --> 02:18.750
No, it's fine.
I got time.

02:20.120 --> 02:22.120
You're okay with both girls
today, right?

02:22.120 --> 02:23.620
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:23.620 --> 02:26.120
Maybe I'll just...
tell them today.

02:27.330 --> 02:31.460
♪♪

02:31.460 --> 02:34.420
I can see you're not
in love with that idea.

02:36.120 --> 02:38.000
I just think it's too soon, Dad.
I think we should wait.

02:38.000 --> 02:39.290
Too soon for what?

02:39.290 --> 02:42.290
♪♪

02:42.290 --> 02:44.380
For me to change my mind?

02:44.380 --> 02:46.290
I just want you to consider
all of your options.

02:46.290 --> 02:47.880
Honey, I have.

02:47.880 --> 02:49.830
And I can't do it.

02:49.830 --> 02:51.500
More chemo is just --

02:51.500 --> 02:53.290
There's things
other than chemo.

02:53.290 --> 02:56.120
There's clinical trials
and alternative medicine.

02:56.120 --> 02:57.670
I'm okay with this.

02:57.670 --> 02:59.830
♪♪

02:59.830 --> 03:01.290
And I can see
that you're not,

03:01.290 --> 03:03.170
and I am sorry
about that, but --

03:03.170 --> 03:05.710
You know what? We don't have to
talk about this right now, okay?

03:05.710 --> 03:08.500
[ Silverware clattering ]

03:08.500 --> 03:09.960
[ Sighs ]

03:09.960 --> 03:11.540
Okay,
I won't tell them.

03:11.540 --> 03:13.420
Okay, good.
[ Drawer closes ]

03:13.420 --> 03:14.710
♪♪

03:14.710 --> 03:15.880
[ Keys rattle ]

03:15.880 --> 03:17.500
I'll see you tonight.

03:18.710 --> 03:20.210
Okay, have a good day.

03:20.210 --> 03:27.710
♪♪

03:27.710 --> 03:29.210
[ Fax machine whirs ]

03:29.210 --> 03:31.790
Hey, uh,
that from the Coast Guard?

03:31.790 --> 03:34.170
Yeah. Just came in.
Thanks.

03:34.170 --> 03:36.290
How long is
she gonna stay here?

03:36.290 --> 03:39.830
Oh, uh, well,
it's protective custody,

03:39.830 --> 03:42.580
so she'll be here until we're
sure Kindred can't get to her.

03:42.580 --> 03:44.620
Mm-hmm. I'm just saying,
this is not a hotel,

03:44.620 --> 03:45.790
and I'm not the maid.

03:45.790 --> 03:46.920
No, un-- understood.
Mm.

03:48.500 --> 03:50.290
We're out of creamer.

03:50.290 --> 03:51.330
Bite me.

03:54.500 --> 03:56.080
Um, morning, Chief.

03:56.080 --> 03:57.330
Morning.

03:57.330 --> 03:58.620
Hey, um,
the Coast Guard

03:58.620 --> 04:00.960
sent the report
on the Wilkis death.

04:00.960 --> 04:03.040
September 2015,
Wilkis set sail

04:03.040 --> 04:04.830
despite a marine warning
that day.

04:04.830 --> 04:06.830
Coast Guard found the boat
adrift with a broken mast

04:06.830 --> 04:08.620
off the coast of Delaware
about a week later.

04:08.620 --> 04:11.000
Never found a body.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.120
Is there any evidence someone
was on the boat with him?

04:13.120 --> 04:16.460
No, whole deck got swamped.
Everything washed away.

04:16.460 --> 04:19.120
I'll talk to the widow.
You canvass the marina.

04:19.120 --> 04:20.750
Four years
is a long time,

04:20.750 --> 04:22.540
but maybe somebody remembers
if they saw him with anyone.

04:22.540 --> 04:24.500
Okay.

04:24.500 --> 04:28.170
We need to discuss the water
pressure in your shower.

04:28.170 --> 04:30.000
I know. I'm so excited
to do that.

04:30.000 --> 04:31.460
It's at the top
of my list.

04:31.460 --> 04:38.580
♪♪

04:38.580 --> 04:41.170
That boat
was everything to him.

04:41.170 --> 04:43.040
Then the job.

04:43.040 --> 04:46.710
I was a...
distant third, probably.

04:46.710 --> 04:48.750
Is it possible someone else
was on the boat with him

04:48.750 --> 04:49.960
when he disappeared?

04:49.960 --> 04:51.420
I can't imagine.

04:51.420 --> 04:53.080
He wouldn't even take me.

04:53.080 --> 04:55.210
Liked the solitude.

04:55.210 --> 04:57.580
So there's no chance
he was with Richard Kindred?

04:57.580 --> 04:59.460
Uh, no.

04:59.460 --> 05:01.330
Zero chance of that.

05:01.330 --> 05:03.380
Is this
about the break-in?

05:03.380 --> 05:05.880
I told the police
nothing was taken.

05:07.380 --> 05:10.580
We have reason to suspect
that your husband...

05:10.580 --> 05:12.080
might have been murdered.

05:13.380 --> 05:14.960
[ Laughs ]

05:16.620 --> 05:19.080
By Dicky Kindred?

05:19.080 --> 05:20.540
No. Never.

05:20.540 --> 05:22.290
Why?

05:22.290 --> 05:25.250
That would be tantamount
to killing the golden goose.

05:27.290 --> 05:30.080
You wanna know a big secret
about Richard Kindred?

05:30.080 --> 05:32.460
He's a fraud.
A con man.

05:34.170 --> 05:36.880
He doesn't know the first thing
about technology.

05:36.880 --> 05:38.540
That is
not at all surprising.

05:38.540 --> 05:40.540
Did you know that your husband
tried to change

05:40.540 --> 05:43.290
the terms of his contract
before he died?

05:43.290 --> 05:45.750
His stock options
would've gone to you.

05:45.750 --> 05:47.250
Instead,
they went to Kindred.

05:47.250 --> 05:48.670
♪♪

05:48.670 --> 05:51.670
No, I did not know that.

05:51.670 --> 05:54.420
But that just reinforces
my theory.

05:54.420 --> 05:57.120
I suspect
Alan killed himself.

05:57.120 --> 05:59.750
Why would you
think that?

05:59.750 --> 06:01.580
He fixed that door.

06:01.580 --> 06:04.880
Used to stick all the time,
for years.

06:04.880 --> 06:07.540
A few weeks before he died,
he fixed it.

06:07.540 --> 06:10.080
♪♪

06:10.080 --> 06:12.790
Looking back now,
I think he was saying goodbye.

06:12.790 --> 06:16.540
I arrested Kindred,
and then I let him go.

06:16.540 --> 06:19.040
And someone just
broke into your house.

06:19.040 --> 06:21.750
This is
not a coincidence.

06:21.750 --> 06:24.790
What might Kindred
have been looking for?

06:24.790 --> 06:27.210
I guess his research.

06:27.210 --> 06:30.000
But Alan never
brought any of that home.

06:30.000 --> 06:33.330
He never even talked
about work.

06:33.330 --> 06:36.620
All that knowledge...
died with him.

06:36.620 --> 06:44.750
♪♪

06:44.750 --> 06:45.920
[ Clears throat ]

06:47.460 --> 06:49.040
[ Whispering ] Do you know
how to ride a bike?

06:49.040 --> 06:51.000
Um...I don't know.

06:51.000 --> 06:52.250
We're gonna find out,

06:52.250 --> 06:54.000
because Dad's coming over
to check on me,

06:54.000 --> 06:56.170
and then
you and I are leaving.

06:56.170 --> 06:57.540
Aren't we gonna
get in trouble?

06:57.540 --> 06:59.210
No.

06:59.210 --> 07:02.460
Because we're gonna be
very quick and very quiet.

07:07.250 --> 07:11.420
♪♪

07:11.420 --> 07:12.790
Hello.

07:12.790 --> 07:16.830
♪♪

07:16.830 --> 07:18.710
It's nice
to see you again.

07:18.710 --> 07:25.710
♪♪

07:25.710 --> 07:27.330
Why am I here?

07:27.330 --> 07:29.120
What do you think?

07:29.120 --> 07:31.290
You brought me.

07:31.290 --> 07:34.250
Not entirely.

07:34.250 --> 07:37.460
I sort of invited you.

07:37.460 --> 07:39.960
But you wouldn't be here
if you didn't want to be.

07:39.960 --> 07:43.080
But...why this place?

07:43.080 --> 07:47.790
I always feel peaceful
when I'm here.

07:47.790 --> 07:49.500
Calm.

07:49.500 --> 07:51.210
I can be myself.

07:51.210 --> 07:54.040
And you can be
yourself, too.

07:54.040 --> 07:56.460
But...

07:56.460 --> 07:58.250
this place isn't real.

07:59.500 --> 08:01.210
What makes you say that?

08:01.210 --> 08:06.120
♪♪

08:06.120 --> 08:11.920
♪♪

08:11.920 --> 08:13.330
My God.

08:13.330 --> 08:15.750
♪♪

08:15.750 --> 08:17.580
You are so smart.

08:17.580 --> 08:24.830
♪♪

08:24.830 --> 08:26.830
Why this place?

08:26.830 --> 08:29.250
Jo showed me
a picture of it.

08:29.250 --> 08:31.710
She said they used to
go fishing here.

08:32.960 --> 08:35.170
You like Jo a lot,
don't you?

08:36.460 --> 08:37.540
Yes.

08:39.080 --> 08:40.290
Why?

08:40.290 --> 08:43.290
♪♪

08:43.290 --> 08:45.580
She feels like home.

08:45.580 --> 08:48.330
♪♪

08:48.330 --> 08:49.210
Hmm.

08:51.540 --> 08:54.170
Maybe someday,

08:54.170 --> 08:56.290
you'll feel the same way
about me.

08:56.290 --> 08:59.080
♪♪

08:59.080 --> 09:00.460
Mia's waiting for me.

09:02.580 --> 09:03.880
Then you should go.

09:03.880 --> 09:07.830
♪♪

09:07.830 --> 09:09.540
I'll see you very soon.

09:09.540 --> 09:14.460
♪♪

09:14.460 --> 09:20.460
♪♪

09:20.460 --> 09:22.880
You seem to want
to provoke me.

09:22.880 --> 09:26.170
Well...
it's not not fun.

09:26.170 --> 09:28.000
You're not a prisoner,
Emily.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
I'd like to keep you safe,
but I'm not gonna

09:30.000 --> 09:32.500
force you to stay here
if you don't want to.

09:32.500 --> 09:34.000
How was the widow?

09:34.000 --> 09:35.210
[ Sniffs ]

09:35.210 --> 09:36.170
I don't know. Sad.

09:37.580 --> 09:39.540
She thinks
Wilkis killed himself.

09:39.540 --> 09:41.620
It's possible.

09:41.620 --> 09:44.120
He had
the mind of a god

09:44.120 --> 09:47.460
but the emotional stability
of a ferret.

09:47.460 --> 09:52.290
Still, I think he was too much
of a narcissist for suicide.

09:52.290 --> 09:53.830
You know...

09:53.830 --> 09:55.080
he designed her.

09:56.040 --> 09:57.420
Is that so?

09:57.420 --> 10:00.170
Not the physical body --
the AI.

10:00.170 --> 10:03.880
He dedicated
his whole life to it.

10:03.880 --> 10:05.620
By the end,
he despised it.

10:05.620 --> 10:07.830
He destroyed
all of the source code

10:07.830 --> 10:10.080
so that no one else
could replicate it.

10:10.080 --> 10:12.620
So how did Kindred
get his hands on it?

10:12.620 --> 10:14.330
My guess?

10:14.330 --> 10:16.790
Threatened to kill him
unless he forked it over...

10:16.790 --> 10:20.000
then killed him anyway.

10:20.000 --> 10:22.960
Hey, uh...you're not
gonna believe this.

10:22.960 --> 10:24.580
Alan Wilkis is...

10:24.580 --> 10:26.000
alive.

10:29.620 --> 10:31.290
Oh, hey.
How's the patient?

10:31.290 --> 10:32.620
Award-winning
performance.

10:32.620 --> 10:33.790
Ah.
She's fine.

10:33.790 --> 10:35.080
[ Chuckles ]

10:35.080 --> 10:36.670
All this
looks like a nightmare.

10:36.670 --> 10:38.290
Oh, no, it's great.

10:38.290 --> 10:41.250
I went from seven remotes
all the way down to four.

10:41.250 --> 10:43.040
I got the instructions
right here. Want me
to run you through it?

10:43.040 --> 10:45.420
That's a big pass.
[ Chuckles ]

10:45.420 --> 10:47.670
You hungry? I make
a dynamite grilled cheese.

10:47.670 --> 10:49.210
[ Groans ]
[ Refrigerator door opens ]

10:49.210 --> 10:52.000
You sound real busted up
about losing your job.

10:52.000 --> 10:54.580
Yeah.
I deserve some time off.

10:54.580 --> 10:56.830
Uh-huh, spoken like
a trust fund kid.

10:56.830 --> 10:58.210
Also true.

10:58.210 --> 11:00.790
Well...

11:00.790 --> 11:03.670
you can make me lunch,
or we can just cut to the part

11:03.670 --> 11:06.080
where you try to talk me
into doing more chemo.

11:07.710 --> 11:09.620
Mm-hmm.
I know she sent you.

11:09.620 --> 11:10.920
Yeah.

11:10.920 --> 11:12.040
She loves you.
I know.

11:12.040 --> 11:14.120
We all do.
Never doubted it.

11:14.120 --> 11:17.750
It's just that she
doesn't understand why
you didn't talk to her.

11:17.750 --> 11:20.790
It's like...
you made the decision

11:20.790 --> 11:22.500
without even
thinking about her.

11:22.500 --> 11:24.250
♪♪

11:24.250 --> 11:26.960
Yeah, I didn't
think of her.

11:26.960 --> 11:29.540
[ Inhales sharply ]
You know what? I --

11:29.540 --> 11:31.170
That was a mistake.
I'm sorry.

11:31.170 --> 11:33.580
How often do you think
of your daughter?

11:33.580 --> 11:34.620
Hmm? Rough guess.

11:34.620 --> 11:36.330
50% of the time?

11:36.330 --> 11:37.920
80?

11:37.920 --> 11:40.750
Yeah. You're right.
I know.

11:40.750 --> 11:42.330
It's just, I --
Did you think about her

11:42.330 --> 11:44.880
when you and Jo
decided to split up?

11:44.880 --> 11:47.420
Eh, you guys just did
what you needed to do.

11:47.420 --> 11:50.710
Even if Mia got hurt,
and Mia did get hurt.

11:50.710 --> 11:54.580
And I didn't chime in
with my opinion because...

11:54.580 --> 11:57.290
it just
wasn't my business.

11:57.290 --> 11:59.330
Ed, I'm still here.

11:59.330 --> 12:01.670
I didn't leave.

12:01.670 --> 12:03.170
I didn't give up.

12:03.170 --> 12:05.790
♪♪

12:05.790 --> 12:07.620
Ask Mia if that's
what she thinks.

12:07.620 --> 12:14.120
♪♪

12:15.750 --> 12:17.750
Benny:
How'd you find him?

12:17.750 --> 12:19.500
I followed the boat.

12:19.500 --> 12:22.750
It was sold at auction about
a year after Wilkis disappeared.

12:22.750 --> 12:24.670
Buyer was an anonymous LLC
called Vector.

12:24.670 --> 12:26.330
That was his cat's name.

12:26.330 --> 12:28.620
Okay, uh, yeah,
the boat itself

12:28.620 --> 12:31.580
was renamed the Ashley Grace
and moored in North Carolina.

12:31.580 --> 12:33.580
That's from
two weeks ago.

12:33.580 --> 12:36.330
The harbormaster says that
he pays cash, keeps to himself,

12:36.330 --> 12:38.420
and goes sailing
a few times a year.

12:38.420 --> 12:39.540
Old habits.

12:39.540 --> 12:41.460
Get you caught.

12:41.460 --> 12:42.540
Great work.

12:42.540 --> 12:44.040
Thanks.

12:44.040 --> 12:45.880
I need you
to reach out to him.

12:45.880 --> 12:47.880
Our only method of communicating
was through a dark web forum.

12:49.380 --> 12:51.000
I can send him
a message,

12:51.000 --> 12:53.040
but typically,
he took weeks to respond.

12:53.040 --> 12:55.540
You have bait now.

12:56.790 --> 12:59.250
I need him
to take a hike.

12:59.250 --> 13:01.420
Excuse me?

13:01.420 --> 13:04.460
♪♪

13:04.460 --> 13:06.460
Chris, why don't you
go get a cup of coffee?

13:06.460 --> 13:16.040
♪♪

13:16.040 --> 13:17.920
Emily:
Show Wilkis the AI.

13:17.920 --> 13:20.420
Show him
what he created.

13:20.420 --> 13:21.880
He won't be able
to resist.

13:21.880 --> 13:25.540
♪♪

13:25.540 --> 13:26.540
Mia: Okay.

13:26.540 --> 13:28.880
Something like that?

13:28.880 --> 13:30.460
Okay, like that.

13:31.880 --> 13:34.420
I think
I figured it out.

13:34.420 --> 13:36.500
You can move metal
with your mind.

13:36.500 --> 13:37.670
Like Magneto.

13:37.670 --> 13:39.420
What's a Magneto?

13:40.670 --> 13:41.960
Doesn't matter.

13:48.920 --> 13:50.420
Okay.

13:50.420 --> 13:51.670
Do it.

13:51.670 --> 13:53.080
I'm afraid.

13:53.080 --> 13:54.920
Piper.

13:54.920 --> 13:57.250
It's just you and me.

13:57.250 --> 14:00.540
And if you can learn
how to control this,

14:00.540 --> 14:02.460
that's a good thing.

14:02.460 --> 14:03.880
Okay.

14:06.210 --> 14:14.580
♪♪

14:14.580 --> 14:15.750
[ Gasps ]

14:15.750 --> 14:19.540
♪♪

14:19.540 --> 14:22.380
Is it working?

14:22.380 --> 14:23.880
[ Laughing ] Yeah.

14:23.880 --> 14:25.540
Keep going.

14:25.540 --> 14:34.540
♪♪

14:34.540 --> 14:35.750
[ Chuckles ]

14:35.750 --> 14:37.880
This is amazing.

14:37.880 --> 14:38.880
[ Horn honks ]

14:40.080 --> 14:41.620
[ Gasps, groans ]

14:41.620 --> 14:43.710
[ Gasps ]

14:43.710 --> 14:45.790
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

14:45.790 --> 14:46.880
It's okay, it's okay.

14:46.880 --> 14:48.000
It was an accident.

14:48.000 --> 14:50.000
Is it broken?

14:50.000 --> 14:51.960
We need to go home.
No. No.

14:51.960 --> 14:53.880
No.

14:53.880 --> 14:55.250
[ Sighs ]

14:55.250 --> 14:56.830
I have a better idea.

14:58.170 --> 14:59.580
Okay.
Okay.

14:59.580 --> 15:02.500
And they want you to pick a date
for a community meeting

15:02.500 --> 15:04.460
about the uptick
in vehicle break-ins.

15:04.460 --> 15:06.920
Daph, can you
just give me a minute?

15:06.920 --> 15:08.580
Sure. No problem.
Thanks.

15:09.920 --> 15:11.920
Hey, Chris. Why don't you
come on in and have a seat?

15:11.920 --> 15:14.210
Hey, uh,
I just want to say that, uh,

15:14.210 --> 15:16.040
if there's something
that I've been doing

15:16.040 --> 15:17.620
that makes you
question my judgment

15:17.620 --> 15:19.120
or question
your trust in me,

15:19.120 --> 15:20.790
then I would like
to have some feedback,

15:20.790 --> 15:22.670
because I feel like
I-I've been sidelined here,

15:22.670 --> 15:23.960
and I don't
really know why.

15:25.540 --> 15:27.210
You're right.

15:27.210 --> 15:29.620
That was a crappy thing to do,
and I'm sorry.

15:31.000 --> 15:33.210
So, you want to -- want to
tell me what that was all about?

15:34.420 --> 15:35.500
Why don't you
take a seat?

15:44.420 --> 15:46.580
I have been...
[ Clears throat ]

15:46.580 --> 15:48.580
keeping something
from you.

15:48.580 --> 15:51.460
From...everyone,
really.

15:51.460 --> 15:55.540
The only people who know
are Emily and Benny.

15:55.540 --> 15:57.750
Um, and Kindred.

15:57.750 --> 16:00.290
And I trust you a hell of a lot
more than I trust any of them.

16:00.290 --> 16:02.710
So I am gonna...

16:02.710 --> 16:03.880
bring you up to speed.

16:03.880 --> 16:04.880
Okay?

16:04.880 --> 16:07.290
All right.

16:07.290 --> 16:08.250
Okay.

16:10.670 --> 16:12.750
[ Exhales deeply ]

16:12.750 --> 16:17.500
♪♪

16:17.500 --> 16:20.710
Alan Wilkis...

16:20.710 --> 16:22.880
designed an AI program.

16:24.920 --> 16:27.460
Emily's idea
to draw him out

16:27.460 --> 16:30.540
was to send him
a video...

16:30.540 --> 16:31.540
of Piper.

16:33.880 --> 16:37.040
Because...

16:37.040 --> 16:40.920
she's a product...

16:40.920 --> 16:42.460
of that design.

16:42.460 --> 16:44.920
♪♪

16:44.920 --> 16:46.670
Piper's AI.

16:46.670 --> 16:52.540
♪♪

16:56.710 --> 16:58.290
Okay. Got it.

16:59.540 --> 17:02.170
I'm s--
You've got -- You've got --

17:02.170 --> 17:04.960
Your response is --
is y-you've got it?

17:04.960 --> 17:06.920
Uh, yep.
Totally clear.

17:06.920 --> 17:07.960
Yeah.

17:09.620 --> 17:11.960
Chris, I don't think --
I mean, I'm -- I'm not --

17:11.960 --> 17:13.790
I-I'm not sure --
Do you -- Do you --

17:13.790 --> 17:15.960
Do you understand
what I'm telling you?

17:15.960 --> 17:18.000
Yeah, artificial intelligence.
I'm good.

17:23.080 --> 17:25.710
Well, you're taking this...
very well.

17:25.710 --> 17:27.830
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

17:27.830 --> 17:29.620
Yeah.

17:29.620 --> 17:31.460
Probably later,
I'll -- I'll freak out

17:31.460 --> 17:34.580
and question the universe
and my place in it.

17:34.580 --> 17:36.420
That sort of thing.

17:38.540 --> 17:39.620
[ Laughing ] Okay.

17:41.170 --> 17:42.920
Uh...

17:42.920 --> 17:45.210
Piper doesn't know.

17:45.210 --> 17:46.540
She cannot know.

17:48.120 --> 17:50.790
I haven't told
Alex or Mia.

17:50.790 --> 17:52.750
My dad.

17:52.750 --> 17:57.580
Uh, and I'm not going to,
because I can't risk anybody...

17:57.580 --> 18:00.000
letting something slip.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
I understand.

18:02.000 --> 18:03.420
[ Knock on door ]

18:03.420 --> 18:04.670
Sorry, Chief.

18:04.670 --> 18:06.120
Uh, delivery.

18:06.120 --> 18:08.290
Yeah, package
for Benny Gallagher.

18:09.790 --> 18:11.380
Yeah, I'll --
I'll take it.

18:11.380 --> 18:13.620
♪♪

18:13.620 --> 18:15.290
Benny's
getting mail here now?

18:15.290 --> 18:18.250
[ Door closes ]

18:18.250 --> 18:20.290
Brookhaven
Central Bus Terminal.

18:20.290 --> 18:22.170
Alan Wilkis
just wrote back.

18:26.040 --> 18:29.880
Woman on P.A.:
...467 arriving from Stanford
is delayed by 18 minutes.

18:29.880 --> 18:33.080
Bus 467 arriving from Stanford
delayed by 18 minutes.

18:33.080 --> 18:35.080
Locker 424.

18:35.080 --> 18:36.460
I haven't seen
anyone near it.

18:38.040 --> 18:39.790
Let's see
what he left for us.

18:39.790 --> 18:43.120
♪♪

18:43.120 --> 18:45.750
[ Sighs ]

18:47.290 --> 18:49.040
"Leave cellphones
and weapons here.

18:49.040 --> 18:50.540
Further instructions
to follow."

18:50.540 --> 18:51.920
Come on.
You're kidding.

18:51.920 --> 18:59.620
♪♪

18:59.620 --> 19:01.960
He's watching us.

19:01.960 --> 19:03.790
♪♪

19:03.790 --> 19:05.380
All right.

19:05.380 --> 19:07.540
Well, I guess I'll contact you
as soon as I'm able.

19:07.540 --> 19:09.170
♪♪

19:09.170 --> 19:10.920
What, are you just
gonna go alone?

19:10.920 --> 19:13.790
Well, I assume a no-gun,
no-communication scavenger hunt

19:13.790 --> 19:15.330
is a bridge too far
for you.

19:15.330 --> 19:18.420
♪♪

19:18.420 --> 19:21.540
All he had to do
was stay quiet.

19:21.540 --> 19:24.210
Just...not respond
to your message.

19:24.210 --> 19:25.960
We would never
have found him.

19:27.620 --> 19:29.460
He's got
something to say.

19:29.460 --> 19:32.750
♪♪

19:32.750 --> 19:34.420
I want to hear
what it is.

19:34.420 --> 19:40.290
♪♪

19:40.290 --> 19:45.330
♪♪

19:45.330 --> 19:46.540
[ Sighs ]

19:46.540 --> 19:48.330
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

19:48.330 --> 19:49.540
Listen.

19:49.540 --> 19:51.750
♪♪

19:51.750 --> 19:54.170
[ Vibrating continues ]

19:58.880 --> 20:00.460
[ Sighs ]

20:00.460 --> 20:03.080
"Space 181.

20:03.080 --> 20:04.790
Keys under seat."

20:04.790 --> 20:08.920
♪♪

20:08.920 --> 20:10.080
[ Keys jingle ]
No GPS.

20:10.080 --> 20:11.330
No Bluetooth.

20:13.210 --> 20:15.170
No one will know
where we are.

20:15.170 --> 20:17.250
I told Chris to check in
every half-hour.

20:17.250 --> 20:19.210
He'll know something's up
when he can't reach me.

20:19.210 --> 20:20.210
And do what?

20:21.710 --> 20:23.540
Excellent police work.

20:23.540 --> 20:25.830
♪♪

20:25.830 --> 20:27.330
[ Car door closes ]

20:27.330 --> 20:30.120
♪♪

20:30.120 --> 20:31.120
Here you go.

20:33.290 --> 20:34.380
All right.

20:34.380 --> 20:35.750
"Route 301.

20:35.750 --> 20:37.290
Mile marker 14.

20:37.290 --> 20:40.880
Do not deviate from map.
Do not contact anyone.

20:40.880 --> 20:42.000
You have three hours."

20:42.000 --> 20:43.710
[ Sighs ]

20:43.710 --> 20:45.500
[ Engine starts ]

20:49.210 --> 20:50.330
[ Doorbell rings ]

20:52.920 --> 20:54.580
Hi!

20:54.580 --> 20:56.000
[ Chuckles nervously ]

20:56.000 --> 20:58.080
Mia, what --
what's going on?

20:58.080 --> 20:59.750
We were riding
our bikes...

20:59.750 --> 21:02.790
and...I fell.

21:02.790 --> 21:05.120
And I figured,
you know,

21:05.120 --> 21:07.250
since your house
is so close by --

21:07.250 --> 21:08.620
Why -- Why aren't you
in school?

21:08.620 --> 21:10.420
She's sick.

21:12.580 --> 21:14.790
I mean...
but she got better.

21:16.380 --> 21:18.000
Hmm.

21:20.750 --> 21:27.040
♪♪

21:27.040 --> 21:33.420
♪♪

21:33.420 --> 21:35.670
♪♪

21:35.670 --> 21:37.580
[ Engine shuts off ]

21:37.580 --> 21:45.580
♪♪

21:45.580 --> 21:47.460
[ Car door closes ]

21:47.460 --> 21:52.120
♪♪

21:52.120 --> 21:54.250
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

21:54.250 --> 21:57.580
♪♪

21:57.580 --> 21:59.790
"Walk 1,200 yards.

21:59.790 --> 22:02.420
38 degrees northeast."

22:02.420 --> 22:08.540
♪♪

22:08.540 --> 22:09.750
We're close.

22:09.750 --> 22:11.710
I think.

22:11.710 --> 22:13.460
Close to what?

22:13.460 --> 22:15.250
A very good spot
to bury our bodies.

22:15.250 --> 22:17.250
He's not gonna resurrect
himself from the dead

22:17.250 --> 22:18.790
just to kill us.

22:18.790 --> 22:21.040
This might be our only chance
to get something on Kindred,

22:21.040 --> 22:22.670
something
that actually sticks.

22:22.670 --> 22:25.670
Plus, I want
to ask him about this.

22:25.670 --> 22:27.880
Piper's program.

22:27.880 --> 22:30.120
He needs to explain
how it works,

22:30.120 --> 22:32.670
what I can expect
moving forward.

22:32.670 --> 22:34.380
Is she gonna grow
or stay the same?

22:34.380 --> 22:35.960
I just...

22:35.960 --> 22:37.960
I need to know
what I'm into.

22:37.960 --> 22:39.790
So...

22:39.790 --> 22:40.960
why'd you and Alex
split up?

22:40.960 --> 22:42.290
Nope.
Very good.

22:42.290 --> 22:44.040
♪♪

22:44.040 --> 22:45.960
And...that's
about 1,200 yards.

22:45.960 --> 22:47.920
[ Birds chirping ]

22:47.920 --> 22:51.170
♪♪

22:51.170 --> 22:53.040
And there's nothing here.

22:53.040 --> 22:56.540
♪♪

22:56.540 --> 22:58.080
What is that?

23:00.120 --> 23:01.500
Is that a camera?

23:01.500 --> 23:03.880
♪♪

23:03.880 --> 23:05.710
[ High-pitched alarm blaring ]
Aah!
Ohh!

23:05.710 --> 23:08.330
♪♪

23:08.330 --> 23:11.500
[ Blaring continues ]

23:11.500 --> 23:13.540
[ Blaring stops ]

23:13.540 --> 23:20.170
♪♪

23:20.170 --> 23:22.250
[ Engine shuts off ]

23:22.250 --> 23:26.750
♪♪

23:31.710 --> 23:33.750
[ Ears ringing ]

23:39.170 --> 23:41.750
♪♪

23:41.750 --> 23:43.750
[ Groans softly ]

23:43.750 --> 23:50.620
♪♪

23:50.620 --> 23:52.250
Where the hell are we?

23:52.250 --> 23:53.380
Damn it.

23:53.380 --> 23:54.460
What?

23:54.460 --> 23:55.960
He got the disk.

23:55.960 --> 23:57.540
And my gun.

23:57.540 --> 23:59.540
You had another gun? I'd have
quite liked to have known that.

23:59.540 --> 24:01.460
[ Sighs ]

24:01.460 --> 24:03.330
♪♪

24:03.330 --> 24:05.290
[ Groans softly ]

24:05.290 --> 24:08.540
♪♪

24:08.540 --> 24:10.790
I've been here before.

24:10.790 --> 24:12.790
What do you mean?

24:12.790 --> 24:20.420
♪♪

24:20.420 --> 24:28.040
♪♪

24:28.040 --> 24:30.290
It's the view
from my beach house.

24:30.290 --> 24:32.710
Little blood in your ears
from the sound cannon.

24:32.710 --> 24:33.580
No permanent damage.

24:33.580 --> 24:35.250
Clean yourself up.

24:35.250 --> 24:40.460
♪♪

24:40.460 --> 24:42.420
You wanna maybe tell me
why that was necessary?

24:42.420 --> 24:44.290
Do you wanna tell me
why you brought a weapon

24:44.290 --> 24:46.040
when explicitly
instructed not to?

24:46.040 --> 24:48.210
Okay, just to be clear, I had
no idea that she had a gun.

24:48.210 --> 24:50.830
Well, you've done
a disservice to yourself.

24:50.830 --> 24:52.620
A bad first impression.

24:52.620 --> 24:54.920
A bad f-- What am I,
applying for a job?

24:54.920 --> 24:56.080
Where's the disk?

24:58.710 --> 25:00.750
It's nice.
Sophisticated technology.

25:00.750 --> 25:01.880
Who designed it?

25:01.880 --> 25:03.000
Kindred.

25:03.000 --> 25:04.210
That's a lie.

25:04.210 --> 25:05.380
Did you look at it?

25:05.380 --> 25:06.580
No.

25:06.580 --> 25:08.500
The little girl
in the video you saw --

25:08.500 --> 25:09.420
that's her.

25:11.620 --> 25:13.330
If what you're saying is true,
that is not a little girl.

25:13.330 --> 25:15.210
That's the end
of the world.

25:15.210 --> 25:17.290
And there's no way in hell
Richard Kindred designed it.

25:17.290 --> 25:19.460
My understanding is
you did.

25:19.460 --> 25:21.380
No, I...
tried to prevent this.

25:21.380 --> 25:23.420
I destroyed everything --
my entire life's work --

25:23.420 --> 25:24.960
to stop this.

25:24.960 --> 25:27.750
Well, Mr. Wilkis,
somebody took all that work,

25:27.750 --> 25:30.120
and they made
a 10-year-old.

25:30.120 --> 25:34.120
♪♪

25:34.120 --> 25:35.790
Maria:
Can you do this?

25:37.580 --> 25:38.580
And this?

25:39.880 --> 25:41.040
And that?

25:42.920 --> 25:45.540
Okay. Come on.

25:45.540 --> 25:47.000
Tell me what happened.

25:47.000 --> 25:48.580
I fell.

25:48.580 --> 25:50.670
And then there was just,
like, this big rock,

25:50.670 --> 25:52.330
and my arm hit it.

25:53.500 --> 25:54.580
A big rock?

25:56.290 --> 25:57.460
Yes.

25:57.460 --> 26:02.580
♪♪

26:02.580 --> 26:04.710
And why aren't you
in school?

26:04.710 --> 26:07.040
Well, I had a stomachache,
and then I felt better,

26:07.040 --> 26:09.330
and Piper wanted
to go bike riding.

26:09.330 --> 26:11.420
Hmm. And your grandfather
was okay with that?

26:11.420 --> 26:13.000
Mm-hmm.

26:13.000 --> 26:15.670
♪♪

26:15.670 --> 26:18.580
Um, Mia said that...

26:18.580 --> 26:19.790
he wouldn't mind.

26:19.790 --> 26:22.380
Hey, so,
is my arm broken?

26:22.380 --> 26:24.330
♪♪

26:24.330 --> 26:25.620
No.

26:25.620 --> 26:27.710
You're gonna have a bruise
for a while.

26:27.710 --> 26:30.380
Okay. Well, thank you so much,
Abbe. We're gonna --

26:30.380 --> 26:32.080
No, no. No.

26:32.080 --> 26:33.620
That's not
how this works.

26:33.620 --> 26:35.830
You came to my house.
You're my responsibility.

26:35.830 --> 26:37.120
What does that mean?

26:37.120 --> 26:39.580
That means you make yourself
comfortable

26:39.580 --> 26:41.670
and I call your father
to pick you up.

26:41.670 --> 26:47.210
♪♪

26:47.210 --> 26:49.460
You've reached Jo Evans.
Please leave a message.

26:49.460 --> 26:50.920
[ Beep ]

26:50.920 --> 26:52.830
[ Receiver clicks in cradle ]

26:52.830 --> 26:54.830
What's that?
Geez!

26:54.830 --> 26:56.080
That, uh --

26:56.080 --> 26:57.920
That is
the Chief's vehicle,

26:57.920 --> 26:59.880
still parked
at the bus terminal.

26:59.880 --> 27:01.750
And both their phones
are going to voicemail.

27:03.000 --> 27:05.500
Wilkis wants them
off the grid.

27:05.500 --> 27:08.710
Hey, um, how hard would it be
for you to locate

27:08.710 --> 27:11.380
one of those, uh,
fitness trackers?

27:11.380 --> 27:12.670
You're right.

27:12.670 --> 27:14.460
Action Jeeves
wears one of those.

27:14.460 --> 27:17.330
Yeah, okay, I don't --
I don't hate the nickname.

27:17.330 --> 27:19.330
Um...do you think
you could find it?

27:19.330 --> 27:21.880
Uh...yeah.

27:21.880 --> 27:24.670
All right, then.
Get in there.

27:24.670 --> 27:27.670
[ Keyboard clacking ]

27:27.670 --> 27:29.040
Action Jeeves.

27:31.250 --> 27:33.460
G.I. Jeeves.

27:33.460 --> 27:34.580
[ Chuckles ]

27:34.580 --> 27:36.000
[ Clacking continues ]

27:36.000 --> 27:37.670
G.I. Jeeves
with the kung fu grip.

27:37.670 --> 27:39.080
Leave.
Yep.

27:40.620 --> 27:41.960
[ Humming ]

27:41.960 --> 27:43.790
What are we looking at?

27:43.790 --> 27:45.420
It's a neural network.

27:45.420 --> 27:47.880
A programming paradigm
that allows a computer to learn.

27:47.880 --> 27:51.670
♪♪

27:51.670 --> 27:53.710
You should destroy it
immediately.

27:53.710 --> 27:55.290
Hey, that --

27:55.290 --> 27:57.460
That's a little girl.

27:57.460 --> 27:59.540
She's smart...

27:59.540 --> 28:01.170
and funny.

28:01.170 --> 28:03.330
She gets scared.
She has empathy.

28:03.330 --> 28:05.170
That's what
you should fear.

28:05.170 --> 28:06.830
She's constantly evolving.

28:06.830 --> 28:08.920
She's constantly
changing her programming.

28:08.920 --> 28:10.170
You think that makes her
more human.

28:10.170 --> 28:11.750
It doesn't.
It makes her more dangerous.

28:11.750 --> 28:13.540
Because we don't know
where it ends.

28:13.540 --> 28:15.960
I gave up everything --
my entire life --

28:15.960 --> 28:17.540
so that
this wouldn't happen.

28:17.540 --> 28:19.540
Well, I mean...
not everything.

28:19.540 --> 28:20.960
I mean, let's be honest.

28:20.960 --> 28:22.540
This place isn't exactly
a hovel, is it?

28:22.540 --> 28:24.620
This is
a very lovely Bat Cave.

28:24.620 --> 28:26.750
You think I want
to live like this?

28:26.750 --> 28:28.500
I-I tried to do
the right thing.

28:28.500 --> 28:30.750
I think you want to do
the right thing, Mr. Wilkis.

28:30.750 --> 28:32.380
It's the follow-through
that's lacking.

28:32.380 --> 28:35.040
You can't even destroy
your own creation properly.

28:35.040 --> 28:37.210
♪♪

28:37.210 --> 28:39.790
Piper isn't the danger.
Kindred is.

28:39.790 --> 28:42.120
So, help us stop him.

28:42.120 --> 28:44.420
♪♪

28:44.420 --> 28:46.000
Piper is her name?

28:47.540 --> 28:48.670
Yeah.

28:48.670 --> 28:51.000
♪♪

28:51.000 --> 28:53.170
I think I have what you need
to get Kindred.

28:58.620 --> 29:00.170
[ Knock on door ]

29:00.170 --> 29:01.880
Prisoner transfer.

29:01.880 --> 29:03.750
Come on in.

29:03.750 --> 29:05.330
They had dinner.

29:05.330 --> 29:06.620
Thank you.

29:06.620 --> 29:08.120
We owe you.

29:08.120 --> 29:12.290
Uh, she's got
a deep bruise on her arm.

29:12.290 --> 29:15.670
So, ice and rest,
lay off volleyball for a week.

29:15.670 --> 29:17.170
What'd she do?

29:17.170 --> 29:19.540
Oh, well, the story is
she fell off the bike.

29:19.540 --> 29:21.290
But she's lying
through her teeth.

29:21.290 --> 29:22.750
They both are.

29:22.750 --> 29:24.710
They were doing something
they shouldn't have been doing.

29:24.710 --> 29:25.710
Hmm.

29:25.710 --> 29:27.460
I'll get it out of them.

29:27.460 --> 29:28.290
Mm.

29:30.380 --> 29:32.210
You hear about Ed?

29:32.210 --> 29:34.420
Yeah.

29:34.420 --> 29:36.080
Jo asked me
to talk to him.

29:36.080 --> 29:37.420
How'd that go?

29:37.420 --> 29:38.830
Not good. Pretty bad.

29:38.830 --> 29:41.000
Sweet of you to try.

29:42.460 --> 29:44.790
You are the weirdest
divorced couple I've ever met.

29:44.790 --> 29:46.460
Mm.

29:46.460 --> 29:47.830
[ Sniffles ]

29:47.830 --> 29:49.670
Oh. You --
You've got a plan.

29:49.670 --> 29:50.670
No!

29:50.670 --> 29:51.710
Oh.
Nooo.

29:51.710 --> 29:53.040
Uh-huh.
Okay.

29:53.040 --> 29:54.580
Just trying to help.

29:54.580 --> 29:55.580
Sure.

29:55.580 --> 29:57.040
No, I --

29:57.040 --> 29:59.380
Uh, where are
my two criminals?

29:59.380 --> 30:01.710
♪♪

30:01.710 --> 30:03.920
[ Mouse clicks ]

30:03.920 --> 30:07.170
In 2011, we were pursuing
the development

30:07.170 --> 30:10.290
of nanotechnologies
in gene therapy.

30:10.290 --> 30:12.620
Kindred tasked me
with proving it worked.

30:12.620 --> 30:14.290
That meant tests --
on humans.

30:15.830 --> 30:18.250
There was a village
in Malawi.

30:18.250 --> 30:20.880
They all volunteered,
and we paid them, but we knew --

30:22.500 --> 30:24.710
...we knew
before we started.

30:24.710 --> 30:25.580
You knew what?

30:25.580 --> 30:27.620
[ Computer beeps ]

30:27.620 --> 30:35.710
♪♪

30:35.710 --> 30:37.120
14 dead.

30:37.120 --> 30:39.040
♪♪

30:39.040 --> 30:41.710
We paid off the families,
the government burnt the bodies,

30:41.710 --> 30:43.290
and it never happened.

30:43.290 --> 30:50.880
♪♪

30:50.880 --> 30:52.960
You're gonna burn
for this, as well.

30:52.960 --> 30:54.830
I know. I should.

30:54.830 --> 30:56.880
[ Alarm blaring ]

30:56.880 --> 30:59.460
♪♪

30:59.460 --> 31:01.920
[ Computer beeping ]

31:01.920 --> 31:04.540
There's someone
in the elevator.

31:04.540 --> 31:06.500
Where's my gun?

31:06.500 --> 31:09.580
In my truck,
about 70 feet above our heads.

31:09.580 --> 31:13.080
♪♪

31:13.080 --> 31:15.000
What are you doing?

31:15.000 --> 31:16.960
Shut down the elevators.
I can't.

31:16.960 --> 31:18.500
[ Glass shatters ]
[ Grunts ]

31:18.500 --> 31:20.620
Do you know
whose bat that is?!
I don't care.

31:20.620 --> 31:22.040
Is there another exit?

31:22.040 --> 31:24.330
Kindred will be
sifting through the ashes.

31:24.330 --> 31:26.330
[ Powering down ]

31:26.330 --> 31:27.330
Follow me.

31:27.330 --> 31:30.330
♪♪

31:30.330 --> 31:32.080
[ Electricity crackles ]

31:32.080 --> 31:33.040
Wait!
No!

31:33.040 --> 31:34.290
Just wait!

31:35.500 --> 31:36.750
Go! Go!

31:36.750 --> 31:38.380
Go, go, go, go, go!

31:38.380 --> 31:41.380
♪♪

31:41.380 --> 31:42.540
Benny: How far up?

31:42.540 --> 31:43.710
Seven stories.

31:43.710 --> 31:45.710
[ Automatic gunfire ]
Go! Go, go!

31:45.710 --> 31:48.960
♪♪

31:48.960 --> 31:51.080
[ Automatic gunfire ]

31:51.080 --> 31:52.580
Keep going!

31:52.580 --> 32:02.250
♪♪

32:02.250 --> 32:03.580
[ Grunts ]

32:04.670 --> 32:06.210
[ Bat clacks ]

32:06.210 --> 32:10.170
♪♪

32:10.170 --> 32:11.170
[ Coughs ]

32:11.170 --> 32:12.170
[ Strained ] Jo!

32:12.170 --> 32:13.880
[ Grunts ]
[ Groans ]

32:13.880 --> 32:15.830
♪♪

32:15.830 --> 32:17.380
Ears!
[ Bat clacks ]

32:17.380 --> 32:19.000
[ High-pitched alarm blaring ]

32:19.000 --> 32:20.620
[ Men groaning ]

32:21.580 --> 32:23.580
[ Groans ]

32:23.580 --> 32:24.670
Come on!

32:24.670 --> 32:30.420
♪♪

32:30.420 --> 32:35.960
♪♪

32:35.960 --> 32:37.290
Hey! Wait!

32:37.290 --> 32:38.670
He's right behind us!
We're still here!

32:38.670 --> 32:40.040
He's right behind us,
Benny!

32:40.040 --> 32:42.000
[ Both grunting ]

32:43.250 --> 32:45.080
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]

32:45.080 --> 32:46.080
[ Door slams ]

32:46.080 --> 32:47.580
Okay.

32:47.580 --> 32:48.750
Wait. Listen.

32:48.750 --> 32:49.960
Do you hear that?

32:49.960 --> 32:52.290
[ Wailing continues ]

32:52.290 --> 32:55.170
[ Both breathing heavily ]

32:55.170 --> 32:57.540
That's Chris.

32:57.540 --> 32:59.500
That's Chris.

32:59.500 --> 33:00.710
Okay.

33:00.710 --> 33:02.750
[ Wailing continues ]

33:05.170 --> 33:07.710
Come on, now.
Straight upstairs.

33:07.710 --> 33:09.580
Pajamas, teeth, bed.

33:10.710 --> 33:12.170
No talking, no nothing.

33:12.170 --> 33:13.920
Hold on.
[ Snaps fingers ]

33:13.920 --> 33:15.000
Phone.

33:16.420 --> 33:17.880
Come on.

33:20.250 --> 33:22.040
One week.

33:22.040 --> 33:23.710
And that's me
being nice.

33:23.710 --> 33:24.710
Fine.

33:24.710 --> 33:26.330
I'm sorry, what?

33:27.750 --> 33:29.330
That's what I thought.
Keep walking.

33:29.330 --> 33:30.960
Alex --
Nope.

33:30.960 --> 33:32.750
I don't want to see
the puppy dog eyes,

33:32.750 --> 33:35.500
and I don't want to hear the
"Alex, I'm so sorry" garbage.

33:35.500 --> 33:37.420
All right? You're grounded, too.
Upstairs. Let's go.

33:37.420 --> 33:39.040
Fine.

33:41.210 --> 33:43.000
Welcome to the family.

33:48.250 --> 33:53.670
♪♪

33:53.670 --> 33:55.620
Mia: This is amazing.

33:55.620 --> 33:59.540
♪♪

33:59.540 --> 34:00.540
[ Thud ]

34:00.540 --> 34:04.580
♪♪

34:08.210 --> 34:10.960
Man: Federal authorities
arrested Augur CEO
Richard Kindred today,

34:10.960 --> 34:12.500
charging him with wire fraud

34:12.500 --> 34:14.380
and conspiracy
to commit wire fraud,

34:14.380 --> 34:16.120
in connection with medical
experiments officials --

34:16.120 --> 34:17.830
[ TV shuts off ]
Ohh.

34:17.830 --> 34:20.540
Wish I could've seen his face
when they knocked on his door.

34:20.540 --> 34:22.000
Yeah.

34:22.000 --> 34:24.120
Oh, come on.
You're not happy?

34:24.120 --> 34:26.790
I mean...
wire fraud is not exactly

34:26.790 --> 34:29.790
an accurate representation
of what the guy did.

34:29.790 --> 34:31.120
He's facing 20 years.

34:31.120 --> 34:32.750
Effectively
the rest of his life.

34:34.250 --> 34:36.120
Is there any word
on Alan Wilkis?

34:36.120 --> 34:38.790
APB is out to everyone
within 100 miles.

34:38.790 --> 34:40.830
If he surfaces, though, we'll,
uh -- we'll know about it.

34:40.830 --> 34:42.620
Yeah, I doubt
we'll ever see him again.

34:42.620 --> 34:44.210
Guy disappeared
for four years.

34:44.210 --> 34:46.250
He's got the IQ
and the means to do it again.

34:46.250 --> 34:50.380
So, uh...
I can go now...

34:50.380 --> 34:51.380
right?

34:51.380 --> 34:53.460
Yeah.

34:53.460 --> 34:55.830
Uh...

34:55.830 --> 34:58.500
I didn't hate you all
as much as I expected.

34:58.500 --> 34:59.790
Nice.

34:59.790 --> 35:01.920
Real -- Real nice.

35:03.830 --> 35:04.960
Bye.

35:11.540 --> 35:13.420
Buy you a drink?

35:13.420 --> 35:15.000
Or seven?

35:15.000 --> 35:16.710
Uh...no, thank you.

35:16.710 --> 35:18.460
I think
I'm gonna head home.

35:18.460 --> 35:20.000
Okay.

35:20.000 --> 35:21.460
See ya.

35:21.460 --> 35:27.880
♪♪

35:27.880 --> 35:29.080
Hey.

35:29.080 --> 35:30.080
Hey!

35:30.080 --> 35:31.750
Where is everybody?

35:31.750 --> 35:33.460
Uh, well, Mia's up
doing her homework,

35:33.460 --> 35:34.920
[ Refrigerator door opens ]
and Piper's up reading.

35:34.920 --> 35:36.000
You're home early.

35:36.000 --> 35:37.620
Yeah, well...

35:37.620 --> 35:39.290
[ Sighs ]

35:39.290 --> 35:41.620
Richard Kindred
is in federal custody.

35:41.620 --> 35:43.170
Well, congratulations.

35:43.170 --> 35:44.290
[ Both laugh ]

35:44.290 --> 35:46.210
Guess we can put that
behind us, huh?

35:46.210 --> 35:48.460
Yeah. Looks like.

35:51.500 --> 35:55.040
You know, I think I might
owe your ex an apology.

35:55.040 --> 35:56.830
Said some pretty harsh stuff
to him.

35:58.000 --> 35:59.750
I'll make it right.

36:06.080 --> 36:08.080
I've taken advantage
of you, Dad.

36:08.080 --> 36:10.120
No. What are you
talking about?

36:10.120 --> 36:13.750
I just assume
that you'll be here to...

36:13.750 --> 36:16.210
take care of the girls,

36:16.210 --> 36:17.920
take care of the house,
me.

36:17.920 --> 36:19.210
[ Chuckles ]

36:19.210 --> 36:22.000
I'm happy to do that stuff,
you know.

36:22.000 --> 36:24.330
I know
it's selfish of me.

36:24.330 --> 36:26.460
♪♪

36:26.460 --> 36:28.250
I want
to keep you around.

36:28.250 --> 36:31.210
I'm gonna be around
for as long as I can.

36:31.210 --> 36:34.710
♪♪

36:34.710 --> 36:38.000
But what I don't want
is to be broken...

36:38.000 --> 36:40.710
be somebody that
you have to take care of.

36:40.710 --> 36:42.710
I would do that, Dad.

36:42.710 --> 36:44.380
I know you would.
I do.

36:44.380 --> 36:47.210
I'm -- I'm just saying
that you don't have to.

36:47.210 --> 36:49.750
♪♪

36:49.750 --> 36:54.080
I'm saying
I want to be myself...

36:54.080 --> 36:56.460
for as long as I can be.

36:56.460 --> 37:00.330
♪♪

37:00.330 --> 37:01.460
Yeah.

37:01.460 --> 37:03.250
Okay.

37:03.250 --> 37:06.330
♪♪

37:06.330 --> 37:07.620
[ Sighs ]

37:11.380 --> 37:14.960
I have
this memory of mom...

37:14.960 --> 37:16.960
just before she left.

37:16.960 --> 37:22.250
♪♪

37:22.250 --> 37:24.790
I had a...

37:24.790 --> 37:27.250
a green coat
with blue buttons.

37:27.250 --> 37:29.540
My favorite coat.

37:29.540 --> 37:32.670
And...

37:32.670 --> 37:35.670
I had lost a button.

37:35.670 --> 37:38.960
And somehow...

37:38.960 --> 37:41.000
she found
a perfect match.

37:43.080 --> 37:44.670
And she fixed it.

37:44.670 --> 37:50.540
♪♪

37:50.540 --> 37:53.120
And then later on...

37:53.120 --> 37:54.790
after she was gone,
I realized

37:54.790 --> 37:57.960
that that was
all part of the plan.

37:57.960 --> 38:01.540
♪♪

38:01.540 --> 38:05.460
Fix the coat,
say goodbye...

38:05.460 --> 38:07.080
and leave.

38:07.080 --> 38:09.250
[ Sighs ]

38:09.250 --> 38:11.250
Jo...your mom --

38:11.250 --> 38:12.580
It's not the same.

38:14.460 --> 38:16.670
I know
it's not the same, Dad.

38:16.670 --> 38:20.790
♪♪

38:20.790 --> 38:22.420
It just feels
really familiar.

38:22.420 --> 38:24.750
♪♪

38:24.750 --> 38:25.880
[ Door closes ]

38:25.880 --> 38:27.250
Alex: Who's home?
Hey.

38:27.250 --> 38:28.290
We're in here.

38:29.460 --> 38:30.920
Hey.

38:32.790 --> 38:34.620
I know what's going on.

38:34.620 --> 38:35.920
Watch this.

38:39.040 --> 38:40.120
Mia: This is amazing.

38:40.120 --> 38:41.750
Okay, what --
what am I looking at here?

38:41.750 --> 38:43.170
She can move things.

38:43.170 --> 38:45.080
Ed, she's moving that
with her mind.

38:45.080 --> 38:46.290
What?!

38:46.290 --> 38:48.120
Nah, it's gotta be
some kind of a trick.

38:48.120 --> 38:49.880
That is not a trick.
This is real.

38:49.880 --> 38:51.460
[ Gasps ]
Can I see that?

38:51.460 --> 38:52.790
Absolutely.

38:52.790 --> 38:54.080
This all makes sense.

38:54.080 --> 38:55.750
This is why these people
are chasing after her.

38:55.750 --> 38:57.250
The girl has some type
of special powers.

38:57.250 --> 38:58.710
No, they did wires
or something --

38:58.710 --> 39:00.500
No. No! No.
Ed, look --

39:00.500 --> 39:07.080
♪♪

39:07.080 --> 39:08.750
Did you d--
Did you delete it?

39:08.750 --> 39:11.710
♪♪

39:11.710 --> 39:13.330
You knew?

39:13.330 --> 39:14.960
[ Sighs ] Did anybody else
see that video?

39:14.960 --> 39:16.420
No. No one else
has seen it.

39:16.420 --> 39:17.790
How long have you known?

39:17.790 --> 39:19.210
I was trying
to keep her safe.

39:19.210 --> 39:21.210
I was trying
to keep everybody safe.

39:21.210 --> 39:22.500
What else is there, Jo?

39:22.500 --> 39:24.750
♪♪

39:24.750 --> 39:26.420
I can't tell you.

39:26.420 --> 39:27.330
I can't.

39:28.830 --> 39:30.290
If she finds out,

39:30.290 --> 39:32.330
there's a good chance
it could be fatal for her.

39:32.330 --> 39:34.080
That doesn't make
any sense.

39:34.080 --> 39:36.000
[ Voice breaking ]
I know.

39:36.000 --> 39:38.540
You're gonna have to
trust me. Okay?

39:38.540 --> 39:39.790
Trust you.

39:39.790 --> 39:41.170
We have to trust you.

39:42.380 --> 39:44.120
But you didn't trust us.

39:44.120 --> 39:45.880
That's not true.

39:45.880 --> 39:48.120
Can you guarantee
Mia won't get hurt again?

39:48.120 --> 39:49.380
No.

39:49.380 --> 39:52.380
I can't guarantee
anything, Alex.

39:52.380 --> 39:54.580
We could get hit by a bus
tomorrow.

39:54.580 --> 39:56.790
Can you guarantee

39:56.790 --> 40:00.790
that Piper won't somehow
accidentally hurt my daughter?

40:02.330 --> 40:03.750
No.

40:03.750 --> 40:06.580
Then how can you expect me
to let Mia stay here?

40:06.580 --> 40:10.330
♪♪

40:10.330 --> 40:11.500
You're right.

40:11.500 --> 40:12.920
I--

40:12.920 --> 40:14.000
What --

40:14.000 --> 40:18.540
♪♪

40:18.540 --> 40:21.170
Dad! I'm sorry!

40:21.170 --> 40:23.460
It was my fault.
It was not Piper's.

40:23.460 --> 40:24.960
Mia, we're leaving.
Let's go.

40:24.960 --> 40:26.500
It's not forever,
honey.

40:26.500 --> 40:28.210
We just want to make sure
you don't get hurt again.

40:28.210 --> 40:30.120
She didn't do
anything wrong.

40:30.120 --> 40:31.620
Please.
Shh.

40:31.620 --> 40:33.580
It's okay. Okay.

40:34.880 --> 40:36.540
I'll call you tomorrow.

40:36.540 --> 40:37.710
I love you.

40:37.710 --> 40:38.790
Come on.

40:38.790 --> 40:44.790
♪♪

40:44.790 --> 40:51.580
♪♪

40:51.580 --> 40:57.500
♪♪

40:57.500 --> 40:58.750
♪♪

40:58.750 --> 41:00.830
[ Car door closes ]

41:00.830 --> 41:04.620
♪♪

41:04.620 --> 41:06.380
[ Crying ]

41:06.380 --> 41:14.830
♪♪

41:14.830 --> 41:16.330
Kindred: Piper?

41:16.330 --> 41:20.710
♪♪

41:23.620 --> 41:25.000
What happened?

41:25.000 --> 41:27.880
Mia got hurt...

41:27.880 --> 41:29.960
because I showed her
what I can do.

41:29.960 --> 41:32.750
And now
everybody is scared.

41:32.750 --> 41:35.710
Well, that's very sad.

41:35.710 --> 41:38.620
But people
are like that.

41:38.620 --> 41:40.750
Scared of what
they don't understand.

41:40.750 --> 41:44.830
You know, you can always
be yourself with me.

41:46.420 --> 41:48.500
But you're not
who you say you are.

41:48.500 --> 41:50.920
♪♪

41:50.920 --> 41:52.580
What do you mean?

41:52.580 --> 41:59.000
♪♪

41:59.000 --> 41:59.960
You lied.

42:01.670 --> 42:03.710
Sort of.

42:03.710 --> 42:07.290
But really,
it was a test.

42:07.290 --> 42:10.000
And you did so well.

42:10.000 --> 42:13.880
♪♪

42:13.880 --> 42:16.670
What happens now?

42:16.670 --> 42:17.710
Now?

42:19.330 --> 42:20.710
We get to have fun.

42:20.710 --> 42:23.670
♪♪

42:28.500 --> 42:35.580
♪♪

42:35.580 --> 42:42.670
♪♪

42:42.670 --> 42:49.790
♪♪

42:49.790 --> 42:56.960
♪♪

42:59.000 --> 43:00.620
♪♪
